Anonymous Wed 24 Jul 2024 15:31:34 No.67665451 Report
Quoted By: >>67665638 >>67667760
>>67664206
I think you need to weight paint some parts of your model. Although "Rig with automatic weights" gets most of the work done, some parts such as the ears, tail or fluff parts might need hand-tuning.
To weight paint using rigify, you need to nagivate to the rig data tab, and under the bone collections, make the layer called "DEF" visible. These are the deformation bones that move the mesh which are controlled by the rigify gizmos.
Although this video doesn't use rigify or the same version of blender, the weight paint workflow is nearly the same: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4fICQmBEt4Y
To select a DEF bone in blunder 4, Ctrl+shift+left click, then weight paint accordingly. Make sure "x mirror" and "auto normalize" is on.
